<title>USA: Polaroid Q1 net shr profit vs loss.</title>
<headline>Polaroid Q1 net shr profit vs loss.</headline>
<dateline>CAMBRIDGE, Mass. 1997-04-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>POLAROID CORPORATION AND SUBSIDIARY COMPANIES</p>
<p>	 Periods ended MARCH 30, 1997 and MARCH 31, 1996</p>
<p>			 (In millions, except per share data)</p>
<p>							   First Quarter</p>
<p>							   1997	 1996</p>
<p>Net sales:</p>
<p>   United States				    $189.3     $178.0</p>
<p>   International				     268.2	283.1</p>
<p>  Total net sales				    457.5	461.1</p>
<p>   Cost of sales				     259.8	280.9</p>
<p>Marketing, research, engineering and</p>
<p>    administrative expenses			178.5	175.7</p>
<p>   Restructuring and other			   ---	110.0</p>
<p>  Total costs					  438.3	566.6</p>
<p>  Profit/(loss) from operations		   19.2    (105.5)</p>
<p>   Other Income					 17.3	 17.6</p>
<p>   Interest expense				   11.4	 11.6</p>
<p>  Earnings/(loss) before Income taxes	   25.1     (99.5)</p>
<p>  Federal state and foreign Income tax	   9.3     (38.8)</p>
<p>expense/(benefit)</p>
<p>  Net earnings/(loss)				 15.8    ( 60.7)</p>
<p>  Shr						     0.35    ( 1.33)</p>
<p>  Cash dividends par common share		 0.15	 0.15</p>
<p>  Avg shares (in thousands)		     45,345     45,572</p>
<p>NOTE: In the current first quarter, Polaroid reported $0.13 per share profit excluding net after tax exchange gains compared to a loss of $0.07 per share before restructuring and other expenses and a gain on the sale of real estate.</p>
<p>Operating profit in the first quarter 1997 was $19.2 million compared to $4.5 million, excluding pre-tax special charges for restructuring and other expenses of $110 million.</p>
<p>As of January 1, 1997, the company changed its method of accounting for translating the financial results of most of its foreign subsidiaries from dollar functional to local currency functional. There was a $9.9 million or $0.22 per share exchange gain in the current Q1.</p>
